de.rwth.i2.attestor.main

Interface AnalysisTask

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    DefaultAnalysisTask, GeneralAnalysisTask, IndexedAnalysisTask

    public interface AnalysisTask
    An AnalysisTask comprises everything that is required to generate and export a state space. The actual implementation is dependent on the actual analysis approach. An analysis task is usually constructed and configured through a corresponding implementation of AnalysisTaskBuilder.
    Author:
    Christoph

        AbortStrategy getAbortStrategy()

        MaterializationStrategy getMaterializationStrategy()

        CanonicalizationStrategy getCanonicalizationStrategy()

      • getInclusionStrategy

        InclusionStrategy getInclusionStrategy()
        Returns:
        The strategy to discharge whether an abstract program state is subsumed by another state.

      • getStateLabelingStrategy

        StateLabelingStrategy getStateLabelingStrategy()
        Returns:
        The strategy that assigns atomic propositions to each generated state.

      • getStateSpace

        StateSpace getStateSpace()
        Returns:
        Before calling execute() this method returns null. Otherwise, it returns the state space that has been generated.
